  "prompt": "How can you delete all photos from your iPhone?",
  "response": "Here are a few ways to delete all photos from your iPhone:\n\n1. Delete all photos manually:\n- Open the Photos app\n- Select \"Select\" in top right corner\n- Tap \"Select All\"\n- Tap the trash/delete icon\n- Confirm deletion\n\n2. Delete from Settings:\n- Go to Settings\n- Tap General\n- Select iPhone Storage\n- Scroll to Photos\n- Tap \"Delete All Photos\" option\n\n3. Reset iPhone to factory settings:\n- Go to Settings\n- General\n- Reset\n- Erase All Content and Settings\n- This will delete ALL data, not just photos\n\n4. Use third-party apps:\n- Some photo management apps offer bulk delete options\n\n5. iCloud photo deletion:\n- Delete photos from iCloud.com\n- This will sync and remove from iPhone\n\n6. Computer method:\n- Connect iPhone to computer\n- Use Photos app or iTunes to delete all photos\n\nTips:\n- Always back up important photos first\n- Consider transferring photos to computer/cloud before deleting\n- Some methods delete ALL data, so be careful\n\nChoose the method that best suits your specific needs and comfort level.",
